.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-stop - Stop services (all if no service specified, or a specific one)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel stop [service] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Stops running services.

.PP
When a service name is provided, that specific service is stopped.
When no service is specified, all services in the manifest are stopped.

.PP
Available services: bonsai, diffusers, extraction, llamacpp, lmstudio, ollama, sglang, transcribe, vllm


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--dry-run\fP[=false]
	Show what would be stopped without doing it.

.PP
\fB-f\fP, \fB--force\fP[=false]
	Skip confirmation prompts.

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for stop

.PP
\fB--rm\fP[=false]
	Remove the container/volumes after stopping.


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Stop a specific service
  citadel stop vllm

  # Stop all services in the manifest
  citadel stop

  # Stop and remove the container and volumes
  citadel stop ollama --rm

  # Skip confirmation prompts (for scripts)
  citadel stop --force

  # Preview what would be stopped
  citadel stop --dry-run
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP
